description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to apply for posts at the UK’s first Academic Health Science Centre. We have posts starting immediately and in March 2021 in general paediatrics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Paediatric Department serves a diverse local population, with 100 languages spoken locally and a broad socio-economic range.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Paediatric department is a strong academic department and the unit provides tertiary referral services for paediatric intensive care, infectious diseases, allergy, neurology, haematology and nephrology. Our short stay unit is a development that is providing exciting and innovative ways of managing children. Our Paediatric A&amp;E department sees over 26000 children each year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively encourage you to visit prior to interview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply on-line for this post. Only online applications will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews are planned for &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;week commencing 23rd November 2020 (TBC)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AIMING TO PROMOTE EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
